---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="How it works | ForgeCore" description="The operating loop behind the ForgeCore autonomous revenue system.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="reading">
      <SectionHeader eyebrow="How it works" title="A practical loop, not a vague promise." description="Each stage should create clearer signals, stronger assets, or better allocation decisions." />
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>Opportunity intake</h3>
        <p>Signals enter from market movement, search demand, platform shifts, operator pain, monetization gaps, and performance data from existing modules.</p>
        <h3>Scoring logic</h3>
        <p>Opportunities are ranked by leverage, ease of execution, defensibility, monetization speed, and fit with the current system.</p>
        <h3>Build stage</h3>
        <p>The system creates assets: pages, newsletters, briefs, tools, templates, workflows, and channel-specific deployment objects.</p>
        <h3>Deployment stage</h3>
        <p>Assets are placed into channels where they can earn traffic, subscribers, leads, transactions, or strategic learning.</p>
        <h3>Telemetry and feedback</h3>
        <p>Performance is observed through the metrics that matter: opens, clicks, signups, conversions, revenue, and operational efficiency.</p>
        <h3>Reallocation logic</h3>
        <p>Working paths receive more attention. Weak paths are pruned. The system compounds by improving decisions, not by multiplying noise.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
